00:30:30.480 --> 00:30:32.000
opposite each other,
that's equivalent.

00:30:32.000 --> 00:30:32.710
It doesn't matter.

00:30:32.710 --> 00:30:35.430
It just-- whether on the
x-axis or y-axis.

00:30:35.430 --> 00:30:39.910
So if you think about this as
a globe, you think about the

00:30:39.910 --> 00:30:46.250
molecule as a globe, so in this
case over there, I put

00:30:46.250 --> 00:30:49.690
all the fluorines on the
equatorial position.

00:30:49.690 --> 00:30:54.180
You can think of this plane at
the waistline as the equator.

00:30:54.180 --> 00:30:57.710
So these are all at the
equatorial position, and the

00:30:57.710 --> 00:31:00.900
electron pairs are
at the poles.

00:31:00.900 --> 00:31:03.540
So the lone pairs are
at polar positions.

00:31:03.540 --> 00:31:06.420
In this case, the lone
pairs are lying

00:31:06.420 --> 00:31:08.790
in equatorial positions.

00:31:08.790 --> 00:31:11.110
Now what do you know about
electrons when

00:31:11.110 --> 00:31:13.400
they get close together?

00:31:13.400 --> 00:31:14.310
They repel.

00:31:14.310 --> 00:31:16.190
And it's a really strong
repulsion.

00:31:16.190 --> 00:31:17.780
That's the Bourne exponent.

00:31:17.780 --> 00:31:21.230
Electron-pair repulsion is
really strong and it'll jack

00:31:21.230 --> 00:31:22.620
the energy way up.

00:31:22.620 --> 00:31:26.110
So if you've got a choice of
putting electrons here close

00:31:26.110 --> 00:31:30.000
together or here farther apart,
which one is going to

00:31:30.000 --> 00:31:32.160
be the lower energy condition?

00:31:32.160 --> 00:31:35.810
This, because this minimizes
electron-pair repulsion, and

00:31:35.810 --> 00:31:38.020
in fact, this is the
one that's favored.

00:31:38.020 --> 00:31:43.010
So by using valence-shell
thought, bonding, nonbonding

00:31:43.010 --> 00:31:45.770
skeletal structure, and then
finally electron-pair

00:31:45.770 --> 00:31:48.410
repulsion, you conclude that
this is the correct form, and

00:31:48.410 --> 00:31:51.210
so you don't see these electron
pairs because we know

00:31:51.210 --> 00:31:53.080
they're really tucked
in tight here.

00:31:53.080 --> 00:31:55.080
What do you see if you
do a spectroscopic

00:31:55.080 --> 00:31:56.270
analysis of this thing?

00:31:56.270 --> 00:31:58.260
All five atoms lie in a plane.

00:31:58.260 --> 00:32:01.610
So this molecule is planar.

00:32:01.610 --> 00:32:05.790
It's planar, just as the sp2
