00:32:19.130 --> 00:32:21.580
So is it polar or nonpolar?

00:32:21.580 --> 00:32:23.590
Where's the net displacement?

00:32:23.590 --> 00:32:26.260
The fluorines are pulling away
from the iodine, but they're

00:32:26.260 --> 00:32:27.840
pulling away symmetrically.

00:32:27.840 --> 00:32:28.960
So there's no net
dipole moment.

00:32:28.960 --> 00:32:31.000
It's cool, huh?

00:32:31.000 --> 00:32:34.650
No net dipole moment, but
net negative charge.

00:32:34.650 --> 00:32:35.560
I love it.

